.TH public_key 3 "public_key 1.20.2" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
public_key \- API module for public-key infrastructure.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Provides functions to handle public-key infrastructure, for details see public_key application.

.PP
\fBNOTE: \fRAll records used in this Reference Manual are generated from ASN.1 specifications and are documented in the User's Guide. See Public-key Records.


.PP
Use the following include directive to get access to the records and constant macros described here and in the User's Guide:

.IP
.nf
 -include_lib("public_key/include/public_key.hrl").

.fi

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBasn1_type() :: atom().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 type present in the Public Key applications ASN.1 specifications.


.RE
.B
\fBbad_cert_reason() ::\fR
\fB          cert_expired | invalid_issuer | invalid_signature |\fR
\fB          name_not_permitted | missing_basic_constraint |\fR
\fB          invalid_key_usage | duplicate_cert_in_path |\fR
\fB          {key_usage_mismatch, term()} |\fR
\fB          {policy_requirement_not_met, term()} |\fR
\fB          {invalid_policy_mapping, term()} |\fR
\fB          {revoked, crl_reason()} |\fR
\fB          invalid_validity_dates |\fR
\fB          {revocation_status_undetermined, term()} |\fR
\fB          atom().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
The reason that a certifcate gets rejected by the certificate path validation.


.RE
.B
\fBcert() :: der_encoded() | #'OTPCertificate'{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
An encoded or decode certificate.


.RE
.B
\fBcert_id() :: {SerialNr :: integer(), issuer_name()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
A certificate is identified by its serial-number and Issuer Name.


.RE
.B
\fBcert_opt() ::\fR
\fB          {digest, digest_type()} |\fR
\fB          {key,\fR
\fB           {namedCurve, oid()} |\fR
\fB           #'ECParameters'{} |\fR
\fB           {rsa, Size :: pos_integer(), Prime :: pos_integer()} |\fR
\fB           private_key()} |\fR
\fB          {validity,\fR
\fB           {From :: erlang:timestamp(), To :: erlang:timestamp()}} |\fR
\fB          {extensions, [#'Extension'{}]}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Options to customize generated test certificates


.RE
.B
\fBchain_opts() ::\fR
\fB          #{root := [cert_opt()],\fR
\fB            intermediates => [[cert_opt()]],\fR
\fB            peer := [cert_opt()]}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Certificate customize options for diffrent parts of the certificate test chain.


.RE
.B
\fBcombined_cert() :: #cert{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
A record that can be used to provide the certificate on both the DER encoded and the OTP decode format.

.PP
Such a construct can be useful to avoid conversions and problems that can arise due to relaxed decoding rules.


.RE
.B
\fBconf_opt() ::\fR
\fB          {cert, der_encoded()} |\fR
\fB          {key, private_key() | {both, public_key(), private_key()}} |\fR
\fB          {cacerts, [der_encoded()]}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Configuration options for the generated certificate test chain.


.RE
.B
\fBcrl_reason() ::\fR
\fB          unspecified | keyCompromise | cACompromise |\fR
\fB          affiliationChanged | superseded | cessationOfOperation |\fR
\fB          certificateHold | privilegeWithdrawn | aACompromise.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
The reason that a certifcate has been revoked as define by RFC 5280.


.RE
.B
\fBcustom_key_opts() :: [term()].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Can be provided together with a custom private key, that specifies a key fun, to provide additional options understood by the fun.


.RE
.B
\fBder_encoded() :: binary().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 DER encoded entity.


.RE
.B
\fBdigest_type() ::\fR
\fB          crypto:sha2() | crypto:sha1() | legacy_digest_type() | none.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Hash function used to create a message digest


.RE
.B
\fBdsa_private_key() :: #'DSAPrivateKey'{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined private key format for the DSA algorithm.


.RE
.B
\fBdsa_public_key() :: {dss_public_key(), #'Dss-Parms'{}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined public key format for the DSA algorithm.


.RE
.B
\fBdss_public_key() :: pos_integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined public key format for the DSS algorithm (part of DSA key).


.RE
.B
\fBecdsa_private_key() :: #'ECPrivateKey'{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined private key format for the ECDSA algorithm.


.RE
.B
\fBecdsa_public_key() ::\fR
\fB          {#'ECPoint'{}, {namedCurve, oid()} | #'ECParameters'{}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined public key format for the ECDSA algorithm.


.RE
.B
\fBeddsa_private_key() ::\fR
\fB          #'ECPrivateKey'{parameters :: {namedCurve, oid()}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined private key format for the EDDSA algorithm, possible oids: ?'id-Ed25519' | ?'id-Ed448'


.RE
.B
\fBeddsa_public_key() :: {#'ECPoint'{}, {namedCurve, oid()}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined public key format for the EDDSA algorithm, possible oids: ?'id-Ed25519' | ?'id-Ed448'


.RE
.B
\fBissuer_name() :: {rdnSequence, [[#'AttributeTypeAndValue'{}]]}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
The value of the issuer part of a certificate.


.RE
.B
\fBkey_params() ::\fR
\fB          'NULL' |\fR
\fB          #'RSASSA-PSS-params'{} |\fR
\fB          {namedCurve, oid()} |\fR
\fB          #'ECParameters'{} |\fR
\fB          #'Dss-Parms'{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined parameters for public key algorithms.


.RE
.B
\fBlegacy_digest_type() :: md5 | md2.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBmldsa_private_key() :: #'ML-DSAPrivateKey'{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ML-DSA private key


.RE
.B
\fBmldsa_public_key() :: #'ML-DSAPublicKey'{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ML-DSA public key


.RE
.B
\fBoid() :: tuple().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Object identifier, a tuple of integers as generated by the \fIASN.1\fR compiler.


.RE
.B
\fBpem_entry() ::\fR
\fB          {pki_asn1_type(),\fR
\fB           DerOrDerEncrypted :: binary(),\fR
\fB           not_encrypted |\fR
\fB           {Cipher :: iodata(),\fR
\fB            Salt ::\fR
\fB                binary() |\fR
\fB                {#'PBEParameter'{}, digest_type()} |\fR
\fB                #'PBES2-params'{}}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Possible \fICiphers\fR are "RC2-CBC" | "DES-CBC" | "DES-EDE3-CBC" \fISalt\fR could be generated with \fIcrypto:strong_rand_bytes(8)\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBpki_asn1_type() ::\fR
\fB          'Certificate' | 'RSAPrivateKey' | 'RSAPublicKey' |\fR
\fB          'SubjectPublicKeyInfo' | 'DSAPrivateKey' | 'DHParameter' |\fR
\fB          'PrivateKeyInfo' | 'CertificationRequest' | 'ContentInfo' |\fR
\fB          'CertificateList' | 'ECPrivateKey' | 'OneAsymmetricKey' |\fR
\fB          'EcpkParameters'.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 type that can be found in PEM files that can be decode by the public_key application.


.RE
.B
\fBpolicy_node() ::\fR
\fB          #{valid_policy := oid(),\fR
\fB            qualifier_set := [#'UserNotice'{} | {uri, string()}],\fR
\fB            expected_policy_set := [oid()]}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Certificate policy information.


.RE
.B
\fBprivate_key() ::\fR
\fB          rsa_private_key() |\fR
\fB          rsa_pss_private_key() |\fR
\fB          dsa_private_key() |\fR
\fB          ecdsa_private_key() |\fR
\fB          eddsa_private_key() |\fR
\fB          mldsa_private_key() |\fR
\fB          slh_dsa_private_key() |\fR
\fB          #{algorithm :=\fR
\fB                slh_dsa | mldsa | eddsa | rsa_pss_pss | ecdsa | rsa |\fR
\fB                dsa,\fR
\fB            sign_fun => fun()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Supported private keys


.RE
.B
\fBpublic_key() ::\fR
\fB          rsa_public_key() |\fR
\fB          rsa_pss_public_key() |\fR
\fB          dsa_public_key() |\fR
\fB          ecdsa_public_key() |\fR
\fB          eddsa_public_key() |\fR
\fB          mldsa_public_key() |\fR
\fB          slh_dsa_public_key().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Supported public keys


.RE
.B
\fBpublic_key_info() ::\fR
\fB          {oid(),\fR
\fB           rsa_public_key() | #'ECPoint'{} | dss_public_key(),\fR
\fB           key_params()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Information a certificates public key.

.PP
Possible oids: ?'rsaEncryption' | ?'id-RSASSA-PSS' | ?'id-ecPublicKey' | ?'id-Ed25519' | ?'id-Ed448' | ?'id-dsa'


.RE
.B
\fBrsa_private_key() ::\fR
\fB          #'RSAPrivateKey'{} | #{algorithm := rsa, encrypt_fun => fun()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined private key format plain RSA algorithm or customization fun.


.RE
.B
\fBrsa_pss_private_key() ::\fR
\fB          {#'RSAPrivateKey'{}, #'RSASSA-PSS-params'{}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined private key format the RSSASSA-PSS algorithm or customization fun.


.RE
.B
\fBrsa_pss_public_key() :: {rsa_public_key(), #'RSASSA-PSS-params'{}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined public key format for the RSSASSA-PSS algorithm.


.RE
.B
\fBrsa_public_key() :: #'RSAPublicKey'{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
ASN.1 defined public key format for plain RSA algorithm.


.RE
.B
\fBslh_dsa_private_key() :: #'SLH-DSAPrivateKey'{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
SLH-DSA private key


.RE
.B
\fBslh_dsa_public_key() :: #'SLH-DSAPublicKey'{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
SLH-DSA public key


.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBcacerts_clear() -> boolean().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Clears any loaded CA certificates, returns true if any was loaded.


.RE
.B
\fBcacerts_get() -> [combined_cert()].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the trusted CA certificates if any are loaded, otherwise uses \fIcacerts_load/0\fR to load them. The function fails if no \fIcacerts\fR could be loaded.


.RE
.B
\fBcacerts_load() -> ok | {error, Reason :: term()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Loads the OS supplied trusted CA certificates.

.PP
This can be overridden by setting the \fIcacerts_path\fR environment key of the \fIpublic_key\fR application with the location of an alternative certificate. You can set it via the command line as:

.IP
.nf
erl -public_key cacerts_path '"/path/to/certs.pem"'

.fi

.PP
Use it with care. It is your responsibility to ensure that the certificates found in this alternative path can be trusted by the running system.


.RE
.B
\fBcacerts_load(File :: file:filename_all()) ->\fR
\fB                      ok | {error, Reason :: term()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Loads the trusted CA certificates from a file.


.RE
.B
\fBcompute_key(OthersECDHkey, MyECDHkey) -> SharedSecret\fR
\fB                     when\fR
\fB                         OthersECDHkey :: #'ECPoint'{},\fR
\fB                         MyECDHkey :: #'ECPrivateKey'{},\fR
\fB                         SharedSecret :: binary().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Computes shared secret.


.RE
.B
\fBcompute_key(OthersDHkey, MyDHkey, DHparms) -> SharedSecret\fR
\fB                     when\fR
\fB                         OthersDHkey :: crypto:dh_public(),\fR
\fB                         MyDHkey :: crypto:dh_private(),\fR
\fB                         DHparms :: #'DHParameter'{},\fR
\fB                         SharedSecret :: binary().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Computes shared secret.


.RE
.B
\fBdecrypt_private(CipherText, Key, Options) -> PlainText\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             CipherText :: binary(),\fR
\fB                             Key :: rsa_private_key(),\fR
\fB                             Options :: crypto:pk_encrypt_decrypt_opts(),\fR
\fB                             PlainText :: binary().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Public-key decryption using the private key. See also \fIcrypto:private_decrypt/4\fR

.PP
\fBWARNING: \fRThis is a legacy function, for security reasons do not use with rsa_pkcs1_padding.



.RE
.B
\fBdecrypt_public(CipherText, Key, Options) -> PlainText\fR
\fB                        when\fR
\fB                            CipherText :: binary(),\fR
\fB                            Key :: rsa_public_key(),\fR
\fB                            Options :: crypto:pk_encrypt_decrypt_opts(),\fR
\fB                            PlainText :: binary().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Public-key decryption using the public key. See also \fIcrypto:public_decrypt/4\fR

.PP
\fBWARNING: \fRThis is a legacy function, for security reasons do not use  with rsa_pkcs1_padding. For digital signatures the use of \fIverify/4\fR together with \fIsign/3\fR is a prefered solution.



.RE
.B
\fBder_decode(Asn1Type, Der) -> Entity\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        Asn1Type :: asn1_type(),\fR
\fB                        Der :: der_encoded(),\fR
\fB                        Entity :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Decodes a public-key ASN.1 DER encoded entity.


.RE
.B
\fBder_encode(Asn1Type, Entity) -> Der\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        Asn1Type :: asn1_type(),\fR
\fB                        Entity :: term(),\fR
\fB                        Der :: binary().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Encodes a public-key entity with ASN.1 DER encoding.


.RE
.B
\fBdh_gex_group(MinSize, SuggestedSize, MaxSize, Groups) ->\fR
\fB                      {ok, {Size, Group}} | {error, term()}\fR
\fB                      when\fR
\fB                          MinSize :: pos_integer(),\fR
\fB                          SuggestedSize :: pos_integer(),\fR
\fB                          MaxSize :: pos_integer(),\fR
\fB                          Groups :: undefined | [{Size, [Group]}],\fR
\fB                          Size :: pos_integer(),\fR
\fB                          Group :: {G, P},\fR
\fB                          G :: pos_integer(),\fR
\fB                          P :: pos_integer().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Selects a group for Diffie-Hellman key exchange with the key size in the range \fIMinSize...MaxSize\fR and as close to \fISuggestedSize\fR as possible. If \fIGroups == undefined\fR a default set will be used, otherwise the group is selected from \fIGroups\fR.

.PP
First a size, as close as possible to SuggestedSize, is selected. Then one group with that key size is randomly selected from the specified set of groups. If no size within the limits of \fIMinSize\fR and \fIMaxSize\fR is available, \fI{error,no_group_found}\fR is returned.

.PP
The default set of groups is listed in \fIlib/public_key/priv/moduli\fR. This file may be regenerated like this:

.IP
.nf
	$> cd $ERL_TOP/lib/public_key/priv/
	$> generate
         ---- wait until all background jobs has finished. It may take several days !
	$> cat moduli-* > moduli
	$> cd ..; make

.fi


.RE
.B
\fBencrypt_private(PlainText, Key, Options) -> CipherText\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             PlainText :: binary(),\fR
\fB                             Key :: rsa_private_key(),\fR
\fB                             Options ::\fR
\fB                                 crypto:pk_encrypt_decrypt_opts() |\fR
\fB                                 custom_key_opts(),\fR
\fB                             CipherText :: binary().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Public-key encryption using the private key.

.PP
See also \fIcrypto:private_encrypt/4\fR. The key can, besides a standard RSA key, be a map specifing the key algorithm \fIrsa\fR and a fun to handle the encryption operation.  This may be used for customized the encryption operation with for instance hardware security modules (HSM) or trusted platform modules (TPM).

.PP
\fBWARNING: \fRThis is a legacy function, for security reasons do not use with rsa_pkcs1_padding. For digital signatures use of \fIsign/3\fR together with \fIverify/4\fR  is the prefered solution.



.RE
.B
\fBencrypt_public(PlainText, Key, Options) -> CipherText\fR
\fB                        when\fR
\fB                            PlainText :: binary(),\fR
\fB                            Key :: rsa_public_key(),\fR
\fB                            Options :: crypto:pk_encrypt_decrypt_opts(),\fR
\fB                            CipherText :: binary().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Public-key encryption using the public key. See also \fIcrypto:public_encrypt/4\fR.

.PP
\fBWARNING: \fRThis is a legacy function, for security reasons do not use with rsa_pkcs1_padding.



.RE
.B
\fBgenerate_key(DHparams | ECparams | RSAparams | MLDSA | SLHDSA) ->\fR
\fB                      DHkeys | ECkey | RSAkey | MLDSAKeys | SLHDSAKeys\fR
\fB                      when\fR
\fB                          DHparams :: #'DHParameter'{},\fR
\fB                          DHkeys ::\fR
\fB                              {PublicDH :: binary(),\fR
\fB                               PrivateDH :: binary()},\fR
\fB                          ECparams ::\fR
\fB                              {namedCurve, oid() | atom()} |\fR
\fB                              #'ECParameters'{},\fR
\fB                          ECkey :: #'ECPrivateKey'{},\fR
\fB                          RSAparams :: {rsa, Size, PubExp},\fR
\fB                          Size :: pos_integer(),\fR
\fB                          PubExp :: pos_integer(),\fR
\fB                          RSAkey :: #'RSAPrivateKey'{},\fR
\fB                          MLDSA :: crypto:mldsa(),\fR
\fB                          MLDSAKeys ::\fR
\fB                              {#'ML-DSAPublicKey'{},\fR
\fB                               #'ML-DSAPrivateKey'{}},\fR
\fB                          SLHDSA :: crypto:slh_dsa(),\fR
\fB                          SLHDSAKeys ::\fR
\fB                              {#'SLH-DSAPublicKey'{},\fR
\fB                               #'SLH-DSAPrivateKey'{}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Generates a new key pair. Note that except for Diffie-Hellman the public key is included in the private key structure. See also \fIcrypto:generate_key/2\fR


.RE
.B
\fBpem_decode(binary()) -> [pem_entry()].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Decodes PEM binary data and returns entries as ASN.1 DER encoded entities.

.PP
Example \fI{ok, PemBin} = file:read_file("cert.pem"). PemEntries = public_key:pem_decode(PemBin).\fR


.RE
.B
\fBpem_encode([pem_entry()]) -> binary().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Creates a PEM binary.


.RE
.B
\fBpem_entry_decode(PemEntry, Password) -> term()\fR
\fB                          when\fR
\fB                              PemEntry :: pem_entry(),\fR
\fB                              Password :: iodata() | fun(() -> iodata()).\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Decodes a PEM entry. \fIpem_decode/1\fR returns a list of PEM entries. Notice that if the PEM entry is of type 'SubjectPublickeyInfo', it is further decoded to an \fIrsa_public_key/0\fR or \fIdsa_public_key/0\fR.

.PP
Password can be either an octet string or function which returns same type.


.RE
.B
\fBpem_entry_encode(Asn1Type, Entity, InfoPwd) -> pem_entry()\fR
\fB                          when\fR
\fB                              Asn1Type :: pki_asn1_type(),\fR
\fB                              Entity :: term(),\fR
\fB                              InfoPwd :: {CipherInfo, Password},\fR
\fB                              CipherInfo ::\fR
\fB                                  {Cipher :: iodata(),\fR
\fB                                   Salt ::\fR
\fB                                       binary() |\fR
\fB                                       {#'PBEParameter'{},\fR
\fB                                        digest_type()} |\fR
\fB                                       #'PBES2-params'{}},\fR
\fB                              Password :: iodata().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Creates a PEM entry that can be feed to \fIpem_encode/1\fR.

.PP
If \fIAsn1Type\fR is \fI'SubjectPublicKeyInfo'\fR, \fIEntity\fR must be either an \fIrsa_public_key/0\fR, \fIdsa_public_key/0\fR or an \fIecdsa_public_key/0\fR and this function creates the appropriate \fI'SubjectPublicKeyInfo'\fR entry.


.RE
.B
\fBpkix_crl_issuer(CRL) -> Issuer\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             CRL :: der_encoded() | #'CertificateList'{},\fR
\fB                             Issuer :: issuer_name().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the issuer of the \fICRL\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBpkix_crl_verify(CRL, Cert) -> boolean()\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             CRL :: der_encoded() | #'CertificateList'{},\fR
\fB                             Cert :: cert().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Verify that \fICert\fR is the \fICRL\fR signer.


.RE
.B
\fBpkix_crls_validate(OTPcertificate, DPandCRLs, Options) ->\fR
\fB                            CRLstatus\fR
\fB                            when\fR
\fB                                OTPcertificate :: #'OTPCertificate'{},\fR
\fB                                DPandCRLs :: [DPandCRL],\fR
\fB                                DPandCRL :: {DP, {DerCRL, CRL}},\fR
\fB                                DP :: #'DistributionPoint'{},\fR
\fB                                DerCRL :: der_encoded(),\fR
\fB                                CRL :: #'CertificateList'{},\fR
\fB                                Options :: [{atom(), term()}],\fR
\fB                                CRLstatus ::\fR
\fB                                    valid | {bad_cert, BadCertReason},\fR
\fB                                BadCertReason ::\fR
\fB                                    revocation_status_undetermined |\fR
\fB                                    {revocation_status_undetermined,\fR
\fB                                     Reason :: term()} |\fR
\fB                                    {revoked, crl_reason()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Performs CRL validation. It is intended to be called from the verify fun of pkix_path_validation/3 .

.PP
Available options:

{update_crl, fun()}
.RS 2
The fun has the following type specification:

.IP
.nf
 fun(#'DistributionPoint'{}, #'CertificateList'{}) ->
        #'CertificateList'{}

.fi

.PP
The fun uses the information in the distribution point to access the latest possible version of the CRL. If this fun is not specified, Public Key uses the default implementation:

.IP
.nf
 fun(_DP, CRL) -> CRL end

.fi


.RE

{issuer_fun, {fun(), UserState::term()}}
.RS 2
The fun has the following type specification:

.IP
.nf
fun(#'DistributionPoint'{}, #'CertificateList'{},
    {rdnSequence,[#'AttributeTypeAndValue'{}]}, UserState::term()) ->
	{ok, #'OTPCertificate'{}, [der_encoded]}

.fi

.PP
The fun returns the root certificate and certificate chain that has signed the CRL.

.IP
.nf
 fun(DP, CRL, Issuer, UserState) -> {ok, RootCert, CertChain}

.fi


.RE

{undetermined_details, boolean()}
.RS 2
Defaults to false. When revocation status cannot be determined, and this option is set to true, details of why no CRLs where accepted are included in the return value.


.RE


.RE
.B
\fBpkix_decode_cert(Cert, Type) ->\fR
\fB                          #'Certificate'{} | #'OTPCertificate'{}\fR
\fB                          when\fR
\fB                              Cert :: der_encoded(),\fR
\fB                              Type :: plain | otp | relaxed.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Decodes an ASN.1 DER-encoded PKIX certificate.

.PP
Option \fIotp\fR uses the customized ASN.1 specification OTP-PKIX.asn1 for decoding and also recursively decode most of the standard parts.

.PP
Option \fIrelaxed\fR is similar to option \fIotp\fR but also allows for empty RDNs in issuer and subject.


.RE
.B
\fBpkix_dist_point(Cert) -> DistPoint\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             Cert :: cert(),\fR
\fB                             DistPoint :: #'DistributionPoint'{}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Creates a distribution point for CRLs issued by the same issuer as \fICert\fR. Can be used as input to \fIpkix_crls_validate/3\fR


.RE
.B
\fBpkix_dist_points(Cert) -> DistPoints\fR
\fB                          when\fR
\fB                              Cert :: cert(),\fR
\fB                              DistPoints :: [#'DistributionPoint'{}].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Extracts distribution points from the certificates extensions.


.RE
.B
\fBpkix_encode(Asn1Type, Entity, Type) -> Der\fR
\fB                     when\fR
\fB                         Asn1Type :: asn1_type(),\fR
\fB                         Entity :: term(),\fR
\fB                         Type :: otp | plain,\fR
\fB                         Der :: der_encoded().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
DER encodes a PKIX x509 certificate or part of such a certificate.

.PP
This function must be used for encoding certificates or parts of certificates that are decoded/created in the \fIotp\fR format, whereas for the plain format this function directly calls \fIder_encode/2\fR.

.PP
\fBNOTE: \fRSubtle ASN-1 encoding errors in certificates may be worked around when decoding, this may have the affect that the encoding a certificate back to DER may generate different bytes then the supplied original.



